TITLE: Comparing Monolithic Classes and Atomic CSS HTML Structure
DESCRIPTION: Shows the differences in HTML markup between monolithic classes and Atomic CSS approaches. Monolithic approach uses a single class for multiple styles, while Atomic CSS uses separate classes for each property-value pair.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/apps/website/docs/react/guides/atomic-css.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: html
CODE:
```
<!-- Monolithic classes -->
<button class="button"></button>
<!-- Atomic CSS -->
<button class="display-flex align-items"></button>
```

