TITLE: Basic Usage of makeStyles in React Components
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to define styles using makeStyles and apply them to React components. This example shows creating a button with red color and an icon with left padding.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/apps/website/docs/react/api/make-styles.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { makeStyles } from '@griffel/react';

const useClasses = makeStyles({
  button: { color: 'red' },
  icon: { paddingLeft: '5px' },
});

function Component() {
  const classes = useClasses();

  return (
    <div>
      <button className={classes.button} />
      <span className={classes.icon} />
    </div>
  );
}
```

