TITLE: Implementing Pseudo-classes with makeStyles
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use pseudo-classes like :active, :hover, and :nth-child in Griffel styles. These rules are transformed to receive a nesting selector.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/apps/website/docs/react/api/make-styles.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import { makeStyles } from '@griffel/react';

const useClasses = makeStyles({
  root: {
    ':active': { color: 'pink' },
    ':hover': { color: 'blue' },
    // üí° :link, :focus, etc. are also supported

    ':nth-child(2n)': { backgroundColor: '#fafafa' },
  },
});
```

LANGUAGE: css
CODE:
```
.fqsesyh:active {
  color: pink;
}
.f10q6zxg:hover {
  color: blue;
}
.fnbrw4x:nth-child(2n) {
  background-color: #fafafa;
}
```

