TITLE: Configuring Webpack with Griffel Loader for JavaScript and TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Webpack configuration example showing how to set up Griffel loader for both JavaScript and TypeScript files. Includes separate rules for JS/JSX and TS/TSX file extensions with TypeScript-specific Babel options.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/apps/website/docs/react/ahead-of-time-compilation/with-webpack.md#2025-04-23_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
module.exports = {
  module: {
    rules: [
      {
        test: /\.(js|jsx)$/,
        exclude: /node_modules/,
        use: {
          loader: '@griffel/webpack-loader',
        },
      },

      // If your project uses TypeScript
      {
        test: /\.(ts|tsx)$/,
        exclude: /node_modules/,
        use: {
          loader: '@griffel/webpack-loader',
          options: {
            babelOptions: {
              presets: ['@babel/preset-typescript'],
            },
          },
        },
      },
    ],
  },
};
```

