TITLE: Creating CSS Keyframe Animations with makeStyles
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to define CSS keyframe animations using the animationName property. The keyframes can be defined as an object with from/to or percentage-based steps.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/apps/website/docs/react/api/make-styles.md#2025-04-23_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
import { makeStyles } from '@griffel/react';

const useClasses = makeStyles({
  root: {
    animationIterationCount: 'infinite',
    animationDuration: '3s',
    animationName: {
      from: { transform: 'rotate(0deg)' },
      to: { transform: 'rotate(360deg)' },
    },
  },
});
```

LANGUAGE: css
CODE:
```
.f1cpbl36 {
  animation-iteration-count: infinite;
}
.f1a27w2r {
  animation-duration: 3s;
}
.f1g6ul6r {
  animation-name: f1q8eu9e;
}
@keyframes f1q8eu9e {
  from {
    transform: rotate(0deg);
  }
  to {
    transform: rotate(360deg);
  }
}
```

