TITLE: Defining Global Styles with Objects in Griffel
DESCRIPTION: Creates global styles including @font-face and body styling using makeStaticStyles. The returned hook is used inside a React component to apply these styles globally.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/apps/website/docs/react/api/make-static-styles.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import { makeStaticStyles } from '@griffel/react';

const useStaticStyles = makeStaticStyles({
  '@font-face': {
    fontFamily: 'Open Sans',
    src: `url("/fonts/OpenSans-Regular-webfont.woff2") format("woff2"),
         url("/fonts/OpenSans-Regular-webfont.woff") format("woff")`,
  },
  body: {
    backgroundColor: 'red',
  },
});

function App() {
  useStaticStyles();

  return <div />;
}
```

