TITLE: Creating Global Styles with makeStaticStyles String
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to create global styles using makeStaticStyles with string syntax or arrays of strings and objects. This provides a more CSS-like approach to defining global styles.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/packages/react/README.md#2025-04-23_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { makeStaticStyles } from '@griffel/react';

const useStaticStyles1 = makeStaticStyles('body { background: red; } .foo { color: green; }');
const useStaticStyles2 = makeStaticStyles([
  {
    '@font-face': {
      fontFamily: 'My Font',
      src: `url(my_font.woff)`,
    },
  },
  'html { line-height: 20px; }',
]);

function App() {
  useStaticStyles1();
  useStaticStyles2();

  return <div />;
}
```

