TITLE: Creating CSS Keyframe Animations with makeStyles
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to define CSS animations using the animationName property with keyframes. Supports both single animation objects and arrays of animation objects.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/packages/react/README.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { makeStyles } from '@griffel/react';

const useClasses = makeStyles({
  root: {
    animationIterationCount: 'infinite',
    animationDuration: '3s',
    animationName: {
      from: { transform: 'rotate(0deg)' },
      to: { transform: 'rotate(360deg)' },
    },
  },
  array: {
    animationIterationCount: 'infinite',
    animationDuration: '3s',
    animationName: [
      {
        from: { transform: 'rotate(0deg)' },
        to: { transform: 'rotate(360deg)' },
      },
      {
        from: { height: '100px' },
        to: { height: '200px' },
      },
    ],
  },
});
```

