TITLE: Basic createDOMRenderer Usage with React
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the basic setup of createDOMRenderer with RendererProvider component for handling style injection in web applications.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/apps/website/docs/react/api/create-dom-renderer.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { createDOMRenderer, RendererProvider } from '@griffel/react';

function App(props) {
  const { targetDocument } = props;
  const renderer = React.useMemo(() => createDOMRenderer(targetDocument), [targetDocument]);

  return (
    <RendererProvider renderer={renderer} targetDocument={targetDocument}>
      {/* Children components */}
      {/* ... */}
    </RendererProvider>
  );
}
```

