TITLE: Using Global Selectors with makeStyles
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to use the :global() selector to associate local styles with global selectors, allowing styles to be applied based on global DOM conditions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/apps/website/docs/react/api/make-styles.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import { makeStyles } from '@griffel/react';

const useClasses = makeStyles({
  root: {
    ':global(html[data-whatintent="mouse"])': { backgroundColor: 'yellow' },
  },
});
```

LANGUAGE: css
CODE:
```
html[data-whatintent='mouse'] .f1xz3i88 {
  background-color: yellow;
}
```

