TITLE: Connecting Local Styles with Global Selectors
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the :global() selector which allows connecting local styles with global selectors. This is useful for styling based on global state or attributes.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/packages/react/README.md#2025-04-23_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: ts
CODE:
```
import { makeStyles } from '@griffel/react';

const useClasses = makeStyles({
  root: {
    ':global(html[data-whatintent="mouse"])': { backgroundColor: 'yellow' },
    // outputs: html[data-whatintent="mouse"] .abcd { background-color: yellow }
  },
});
