TITLE: Configuring Griffel Renderer for Child Windows in React
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to set up a custom renderer for Griffel's makeStyles() by creating a React component that uses RendererProvider with a targetDocument. This configuration allows styles to be properly rendered in child windows, iframes, or Shadow DOM.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/apps/website/docs/react/guides/child-window-rendering.md#2025-04-23_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: jsx
CODE:
```
import { createDOMRenderer, RendererProvider } from '@griffel/react';
import React from 'react';

function MyComponent(props) {
  const { children, targetDocument } = props;
  const renderer = React.useMemo(() => createDOMRenderer(targetDocument), [targetDocument]);

  return (
    <RendererProvider renderer={renderer} targetDocument={targetDocument}>
      {children}
    </RendererProvider>
  );
}
```

