TITLE: Comparing Monolithic and Atomic CSS Implementations
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates how CSS rules are defined in both monolithic and Atomic CSS approaches. Monolithic classes combine multiple properties in a single rule, while Atomic CSS creates separate rules for each property-value pair.
SOURCE: https://github.com/microsoft/griffel/blob/main/apps/website/docs/react/guides/atomic-css.md#2025-04-23_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: css
CODE:
```
/* Monolithic classes */
.button {
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}

/* Atomic CSS */
.display-flex {
  display: flex;
}
.align-items-center {
  align-items: center;
}
```

